**Full Text**:
People love to tell you what's reasonable.
Hire a team.
Raise some money.
Build the org chart.
Grow the headcount.
That's how you prove you're serious.
How you show the world you're building something "real."
I ignored all of that.
Instead, I built a tiny little one-person show.
Just me, a laptop, and a bet that people would care.
Seven years later, that one-person business crossed $15M, and I still have no team and no outside money. 

**My Note**:
If you start seeing repeated mechanics across authors, you’ve moved from collecting posts → building a playbook.
